  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.19.1\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nFound what I believe to be an error at the docs:\r\n\r\nThe [Hardhat-Foundry](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/advanced/hardhat-and-foundry#integrating-with-foundry) article in the docs has two main sections:\r\n1. [Adding Foundry to a Hardhat project](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/advanced/hardhat-and-foundry#adding-foundry-to-a-hardhat-project)\r\n2. [Adding Hardhat to a Foundry project](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/advanced/hardhat-and-foundry#adding-hardhat-to-a-foundry-project)\r\n\r\nThe first section is fine, but the second step misses the steps to install a crucial dependency.\r\nSee a basic hardhat project initialized normally will have [hardhat-toolbox](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/plugins/nomicfoundation-hardhat-toolbox) installed by default.\r\nBut when you follow the steps in section number 2, the steps only include installing the hardhat-foundry plugin, not the Hardhat-toolbox plugin.\r\nThere needs to be an extra step documented that tells folks to install the toolbox plugin so that the most basic Hardhat test functionalities are supported by default.\r\n\r\nI would love to make a PR if possible.\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nFollow the steps at this exact link:\r\n\r\n[https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/advanced/hardhat-and-foundry#adding-hardhat-to-a-foundry-project](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/advanced/hardhat-and-foundry#adding-hardhat-to-a-foundry-project)\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\n_No response_",
